<p>Let's say I have an EJB.</p>  <pre><code>@Stateless public class PersistenceService {      @PersistenceContext(unitName="dependent")     private transient EntityManager entityManager; } </code></pre>  <p>Is there any way to control the <code>unitName</code> value from the clients?</p>  <pre><code>@RequestScoped @Path("/persistence") public class PersistenceResource {      //"some"     @Inject     private transient PersistenceService somePU;      //"other"     @Inject     private transient PersistenceService otherPU; } </code></pre>